President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 2016 as Jewish American Heritage Month. In the proclamation, he acknowledges the significant contributions of Jewish Americans to the United States and highlights their role in shaping the country's character. He emphasizes the importance of ridding the world of bigotry and injustice and reflects on the ways in which Jewish Americans have fought for equality and justice, drawing on lessons from their own history. The proclamation also addresses the rise of anti-Semitism and emphasizes the need to combat prejudice. President Obama reaffirms the commitment to Israel's security and the strong relationship between the United States and Israel. He calls upon all Americans to observe Jewish American Heritage Month and learn more about the heritage and contributions of Jewish Americans.